column5: Not getting any PM's so doing my research the old fashion way. Wanna fish inland lake rainbows to start off my vacation. Is there an online site with links to PDF for the stocking list? Been googling for a while and can find some stuff but not what I'm looking for.
Quite a few lakes with bows in Haliburton, this site lists the MNR data as well as the HHOA data for the last few years  http://hhoa.on.ca/hatchery/stocking
I'm getting different info on stocking numbers from FishOnline and your link. Is it possible this is only the clubs stocking list?
I sent you a message.  Did you not get it?
How far do you want to travel, I have heard good things about the espanola area.
Want to stay around Algonquin Going to head in there after the long weekend and the crowds leave

you may already have this one, but if not, you click on a specific lake and it will give you the species present and previous stocking numbers  http://www.web2.mnr.gov.on.ca/fish_online/fishing/fishingExplorer_en.html  let me know if you're trying Haliburton, I might have a tip
